Upstream daemon (InputPlumber)
------------------------------

This plugin installs the InputPlumber input-routing daemon on
distributions that do not ship it natively. InputPlumber itself is an
independent project owned by ShadowBlip, distributed under
GPL-3.0-or-later:

  https://github.com/ShadowBlip/InputPlumber
  Copyright (c) ShadowBlip contributors, GPL-3.0-or-later.

We do not bundle, vendor, or redistribute InputPlumber's source code or
binaries. The plugin downloads the upstream release tarball directly
from `https://github.com/ShadowBlip/InputPlumber/releases/latest` (or
defers to the user's distribution package manager) at install time, on
the user's machine, at the user's request. The end user therefore
receives InputPlumber from upstream under its native GPL-3.0 terms;
this plugin is a thin installer wrapper around that flow.

The plugin's own source code (the install/status backend and React
panel under `plugins/input-plumber/`) is original work and is not a
derivative of InputPlumber. It interfaces with InputPlumber only
through its public, documented surface (the upstream tarball layout
and the systemd service unit).


libiio runtime dependency
-------------------------

The fallback tarball install path stages `libiio.so.0` next to the
InputPlumber binary so the daemon is self-contained on
read-only-/usr distributions (rpm-ostree). `libiio` is BSD-3-Clause:

  https://github.com/analogdevicesinc/libiio
  Copyright (c) Analog Devices Inc. and contributors, BSD-3-Clause.

We do not modify libiio. The `.so` is copied from the user's existing
system installation (or downloaded fresh from the user's package
manager); we do not bundle a libiio binary in this repository.
